  instructions: ["Make sure butter is fully softened at room temperature — this is key to a smooth, fluffy frosting.", "Beat butter with an electric mixer on medium-high speed for 3–4 minutes until pale and creamy.", "Add sifted powdered sugar one cup at a time, beating on low after each addition to avoid a sugar cloud.", "Add vanilla extract and a pinch of salt. Pour in heavy cream one tablespoon at a time until you reach a spreadable consistency.", "Beat on medium-high for another 2 minutes until light and fluffy.", "Use immediately to frost cakes or cupcakes, or store in the fridge for up to 5 days. Re-whip before using if refrigerated."]
