  instructions: ["Make the sugar syrup first — combine sugar, water, and lemon juice in a saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes until slightly thickened. Set aside to cool completely.", "Shred or roughly chop the kataifi dough into shorter strands. Toss thoroughly with melted butter until every strand is well coated.", "Heat heavy cream in a small saucepan until just simmering. Pour over chopped chocolate, let sit 2 minutes, then stir until a smooth ganache forms. Mix in pistachio paste.", "Press half the buttered kataifi firmly and evenly into a greased baking pan or skillet to form the base layer.", "Spread the chocolate pistachio ganache evenly over the kataifi base. Top with the remaining kataifi and press down firmly.", "Bake at 375°F (190°C) for 25–30 minutes until the top is deep golden and crispy all over.", "Immediately pour the cooled sugar syrup evenly over the hot kunafa. Garnish generously with crushed pistachios and serve warm."]
